    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Standard">
        <prj:name>SiO Maser Observations</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We will conduct a single-pointing search for SiO v=1 J=2-1 stellar masers in the Galactic Center up to very high velocities using four spectral windows.  One spectral window is centered on v=0 km/s, and the other three are offset by 930 MHz (one red, two blue).  The objectives are (1) to detect new high velocity maser-emitting stars, (2) to detect known 43 GHz masers at 86 GHz, (3) to obtain precise positions for the masers, and (4) to measure accelerations and proper motions of previously known SiO masers in the inner parsec.</prj:note>
